parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
stalls
or hesitates while driving
especially when accelerating or going uphill; the transmission slips or jerks; the vehicle is unable to shift into gear; the RPMs rev high when accelerating; the vehicle goes into limp mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or jerking can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or jerks while driving
especially when accelerating or going uphill; the vehicle loses power or stalls; the RPMs rev high when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can cause the airbag to not deploy in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the passenger airbag is deactivated
the airbag does not deploy in a crash
the airbag sensor is not operating
the OCS (Occupant Classification System) sensor is not detecting an adult occupant in the passenger seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can cause serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag did not deploy in a crash
the airbag warning light is illuminated
the vehicle was involved in a crash and the airbag did not deploy
the airbag did not deploy despite the severity of the crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to properly repair a recall can cause the airbag system to malfunction, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The dealership failed to properly repair a recall
the recall repair was not completed
the airbag system is still malfunctioning after the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

symptoms: The brake pedal travels further than normal
